answer.p:
 Using height equals area divided by base, the heights of the three blocks
	    are 2.0=20/(10-0), 2.5=50/(30-10),
	    and 1.5=30/(50-30), respectively. The percentile rank
	    for X=8.0 is the total area to the left
	    of X=8.0, which is 8\cdot 2 =
	    16\%. The X value with 80th percentile must be
	    somewhere between 30 and 50 (because 30 is given to be 70th
	    percentile). Solve (X-30)\cdot 1.5 = 10 to
	    get X\approx 36.7.


	      X \amp\spacer\amp \text{percentile rank}


	      	       \rule{.3in}{.1ex} \amp \amp \rule{1.2in}{.1ex}


	      8.0 \amp\spacer\amp 16\text{th percentile}


	      25.0 \amp\spacer\amp 58\text{th percentile}


	     42.0 \amp\spacer\amp 88\text{rd percentile}


	      18.0 \amp\spacer\amp 40\text{th percentile}


	      36.7 \amp\spacer\amp 80\text{th percentile}

