introduction.p:
Problems 1 and 2 are about the following situation: A box contains seven tickets, labeled a,b,c,d,e,f,g. In Game 1,
    tickets are drawn from the box with replacement. In Game 2, tickets
    are drawn without replacement. On any given draw, every ticket
    remaining in the box is equally likely to be selected on the next
      draw.
      Consider the following events.

	E \amp= \text{get the ticket } a \text{ on draw 1}

	F \amp= \text{get the ticket } b \text{ on draw 2}

	G \amp= \text{get two vowels in the first two draws}

	H \amp= \text{get exactly two vowels in the first seven draws}
